COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.procedure_version IS 'Procedure version informed by the fragment.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.step IS 'Optional step to which the fragment applies.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.knowledge_form IS 'Tacit, Implicit, Explicit, SituatedJudgment, LessonLearned, or another declared form.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.statement IS 'Captured knowledge statement.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.elicitation_session IS 'Optional elicitation session that produced the fragment.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.source_agent IS 'Practitioner or source agent.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.confidence IS 'Low, Medium, or High confidence.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.valid_from IS 'Start of the fragment''s valid-time interval.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.valid_to IS 'End of the fragment''s valid-time interval.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.status IS 'Draft, Reviewed, Approved, Rejected, or Superseded.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.owner_role IS 'Role accountable for maintaining the fragment.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.evaluation_context IS 'The evaluation context this row''s time-dependent witnesses are judged under.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.last_reviewed_at IS 'When this fragment was last actually reviewed and reaffirmed by its owning role. Null when it has never been reviewed since authoring. IsOverdueForReview infers recency from ValidFrom, which records when the claim became TRUE, not when anyone last looked at it. Those are different events, and the inference is deliberately left in place under its own name rather than silently rewritten to fall back on this column.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN knowledge_fragments.semantic_type_iri IS 'Extension class IRI.';

